
int maxGuest(int arr[], int dep[], int n){

    Arrays.sort(arr);                      // sort arrival times
    Arrays.sort(dep);                      // sort departure times

    int i = 1, j = 0;                      // i → arrival pointer, j → departure pointer
    int res = 1, curr = 1;                 // res → max guests, curr → current guests

    while(i < n && j < n){                 // process all events

        if(arr[i] <= dep[j]){              // new guest arrives before previous leaves
              i++;                         
              curr++;                      // increase current count
        }
        else{
              j++;                         
              curr--;                      // guest leaves
        }

        res = Math.max(curr, res);         // update maximum guests
    }

    return res;                            // return maximum guests at any time
}

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Meeting Maximum Guests in Java
Given two arrays, arr[] and dep[] representing the arrival and departure times of guests at a party, where each arrival corresponds to a departure at the same index, the goal is to find the maximum number of guests present at any moment.

Example:

Input:
arr[] = {900, 940}
dep[] = {1000, 1030}

Output: 2

Explanation: The maximum number of guests present at the same time is 2, between 9:40 and 10:00.
